definitions.definition: To lay down; to place; to put.
examples: A crocodile deposits her eggs in the sand.
The waters deposited a rich alluvium.

definitions.definition: To lay up or away for safekeeping; to put up; to store.
examples: to deposit goods in a warehouse

definitions.definition: To entrust one's assets to the care of another. Sometimes done as collateral .
To put money or funds into an account.
examples: I had to deposit two months' rent into my landlord's account before he gave me the keys.

definitions.definition: To lay aside; to rid oneself of.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To lay down; to place; to put.
